And it&#39;s also important that the Ant task includes a reference to the defined
classpath property, and forks a new JVM with that classpath, as in:

    &lt;target name=&quot;test&quot; depends=&quot;compile.tests&quot; if=&quot;junit.present&quot;&gt;
        &lt;junit fork=&quot;yes&quot; printsummary=&quot;no&quot; haltonfailure=&quot;yes&quot;&gt;
            &lt;classpath refid=&quot;classpath&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;formatter type=&quot;plain&quot; usefile=&quot;false&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;test name=&quot;com.whatever.MyTest&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;/junit&gt;
    &lt;/target&gt;


